==English==
===Etymology===
Named by [[w:Leonhard Euler|Leonhard Euler]] after the 17th century mathematician [[w:John Pell|John Pell]], whom Euler mistakenly believed to be the first to find a general solution.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}
# {{numbertheory}} The [[diophantine equation]] <math>x^2 - my^2 = 1</math> for a given integer ''m'', to be solved in integers ''x'' and ''y''.
